{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875629915,"sessionID":"ses_28592529bffe3Ymh1wXB2la5kq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6dc06b001AYbsgxM13vRQfu","messageID":"msg_d7a6dae4a001KgybA7HqC1I8Z8","sessionID":"ses_28592529bffe3Ymh1wXB2la5kq","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_5ad8defd8bf4496f885ef37d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (directories, key files)\n2. Any existing tasks.md files or similar checklists - find their format and conventions\n3. Any existing Dockerfile or docker-related files\n4. Any AR-XXX or ST-XXX references in the codebase to understand the naming conventions\n5. Look for any spec documents, design docs, or planning files related to AR-032 or docker multi-stage builds\n\nReturn:\n- Project structure overview\n- Format/conventions used in existing tasks.md files (show exact template if found)\n- Any existing Dockerfile content\n- Any references to AR-032, ST-3, or docker module specs\n- The path where tasks.md should be created","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285922dcfffeNBQRq5vYutfPNT (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is the comprehensive exploration report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThis is **SDD-TEE v5.1** (Specification-Driven Development -- Token Efficiency Evaluation), a benchmark framework that measures token consumption of AI coding assistants building the open-source **AgentCube** project (a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents).\n\n### Root-level layout (`/home/dsj/benchmark/`):\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/\n├── .gitignore\n├── Makefile                    # Unified entry for benchmark operations\n├── README.md\n├── PLAN.md                     # AR-023 through AR-043 mapping\n├── PROPOSAL.md / proposal.md\n├── requirements.txt\n├── configs/                    # litellm_config.yaml, config.yaml\n├── docs/                       # Token metric design docs\n├── scripts/                    # report.py (AR definitions), etc.\n├── specs/                      # Base specifications per domain\n│   ├── project.md\n│   ├── test_spec.md\n│   ├── testing/\n│   ├── ci-cd/\n│   ├── cli-toolkit/\n│   ├── code-execution/\n│   ├── deployment/             # <-- docker spec lives here\n│   ├── idle-cleanup/\n│   ├── integrations/\n│   ├── python-sdk/\n│   ├── sandbox-orchestration/\n│   ├── session-routing/\n│   └── session-store/\n├── results/                    # Benchmark run results\n└── workspaces/                 # Per-model run workspaces\n    └── v5.1/\n        └── opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/  <-- CURRENT WORKSPACE\n```\n\n### Current workspace layout (`.../opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/`):\n\n```\nworkspace/\n├── changes/                    # AR-001 through AR-032 (Architecture Records)\n│   ├── AR-001/ ... AR-032/    # Each contains: proposal.md, design.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md\n├── cmd/                        # Go binaries: agentd/, cli/, picod/, router/, workloadmanager/\n├── pkg/                        # Go packages: agentd/, apis/, common/, picod/, router/, store/, workloadmanager/\n├── client-go/                  # Generated K8s client\n├── manifests/                  # Helm chart: charts/base/\n├── docker/                     # (to be created by AR-032)\n├── Makefile                    # Build targets\n├── go.mod / go.sum\n├── specs/ (symlinks to /home/dsj/benchmark/specs/)\n├── tasks.md                    # Root-level task file (legacy)\n├── delta-spec.md               # Root-level delta spec (legacy)\n├── design.md                   # Root-level design (legacy)\n├── proposal.md                 # Root-level proposal (legacy)\n└── test/ testing/              # Test directories\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Naming Conventions: AR-XXX and ST-XXX\n\n### AR (Architecture Requirement) numbering:\n- Format: `AR-NNN` (zero-padded 3 digits, e.g., AR-001 through AR-043)\n- Defined in `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/report.py` (line 112):\n  ```python\n  {\"id\": \"AR-032\", \"name\": \"Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\", \"module\": \"docker\", \"lang\": \"Dockerfile\",\n   \"type\": \"新功能\", \"size\": \"S\", \"est_loc\": 150, \"est_files\": 3, \"est_tasks\": 3},\n  ```\n\n### ST (Stage) numbering:\n- Format: `ST-N` (single digit, 0-7)\n- Represents the 8-stage SDD workflow:\n  - ST-0: Proposal\n  - ST-1: Design\n  - ST-2: Delta Spec\n  - ST-3: Tasks\n  - ST-4: Implementation\n  - ST-5: Code Review\n  - ST-6: Verification\n  - ST-7: Archive\n\n### AR directory convention:\nEach AR lives in `changes/AR-NNN/` with exactly 4 files:\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, architecture summary\n- `design.md` -- Full technical design (7 sections: Architecture, Data Structures, API Contracts, Error Handling, Testing Strategy, Implementation Steps, Follow-up Changes)\n- `delta-spec.md` -- GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios\n- `tasks.md` -- Task checklist with sub-tasks, verification commands, dependency graph\n\n---\n\n## 3. tasks.md Format/Conventions\n\nThere are **two distinct tasks.md formats** used across workspaces. The **current workspace** (qwen3.6-plus) uses the **T-NNN format** with sub-tasks:\n\n### Format A (Current workspace -- AR-031, AR-030 -- fully populated):\n\n```markdown\n# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** manifests\n> **Language:** YAML\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-031/design.md`, `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** AR-030 (Helm Chart 模板与 Values) 基线已就位\n\n---\n\n## T-001: values.yaml 新增 RBAC 控制键\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 在 `workloadmanager` 下添加 `rbac.create: true`，含注释说明默认开启以保持向后兼容\n- [ ] T-001.02 在 `volcano.scheduler` 下添加 `rbac.create: \"\"`，含注释说明空字符串表示跟随 `enabled`\n- [ ] T-001.03 确认 `router.rbac.create: false` 已存在且保持不变\n\n**验收**: `python3 -c \"import yaml; d=yaml.safe_load(open('manifests/charts/base/values.yaml')); assert ...\"` 无报错\n\n---\n\n## T-002: _helpers.tpl 新增 RBAC 命名辅助函数\n...\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-001 (values.yaml) ──┬── T-002 (_helpers.tpl) ──┬── T-003 (WM RBAC) ──┐\n                       │                          ├── T-004 (Router RBAC)├── T-005 (delete old)\n                       │                          └── T-006 (Volcano RBAC)\n...\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-001 (values.yaml) | None |\n| G2 | T-002 (_helpers.tpl) | G1 |\n...\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | values.yaml 含三个 RBAC 键且值正确 | `python3 -c \"import yaml; ...\"` |\n| AC2 | _helpers.tpl 含 rbacName 和 rbacBindingName | `grep -c \"...\"` → 2 |\n...\n```\n\n### Format B (Current workspace -- AR-032 scaffold -- empty template):\n\n```markdown\n# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** docker\n> **Language:** Dockerfile\n> **Size:** S\n> **Precondition:** <!-- TODO: e.g. Stage ST-3 (Design) completed -->\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-032/design.md`, `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** <!-- TODO: list dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n## T-001: <!-- TODO: Task title -->\n\n<!-- TODO: Task checklist items -->\n\n**验收**: <!-- TODO: Acceptance verification command -->\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n<!-- TODO: Add dependency graph -->\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n<!-- TODO: List parallelizable task groups -->\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n<!-- TODO: List acceptance criteria with verification commands -->\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n```\n\n### Key conventions observed:\n1. **Title**: `# AR-NNN — Chinese Name (English hint) — Tasks`\n2. **Metadata block**: `> **Key:** value` for Module, Language, Size, Precondition, Reference, Dependency\n3. **Task sections**: `## T-NNN: Task Title` with sub-tasks `- [ ] T-NNN.NN description`\n4. **Verification line**: `**验收**: command` after each task group\n5. **Dependency Graph**: ASCII art diagram\n6. **Parallelizable Groups**: Table with Group/Tasks/Prerequisites\n7. **Acceptance Criteria**: Table with #/Criterion/Command columns\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Dockerfile Content\n\n**No Dockerfiles exist yet in the current workspace.** The `docker/` directory has not been created. AR-032 is the task to create them.\n\nHowever, the **delta-spec.md** and **design.md** for AR-032 are fully populated with the specification:\n\n### Expected Dockerfiles (from design.md):\n\n| File | Binary | Builder Base | Runtime Base | Non-root User |\n|------|--------|-------------|-------------|---------------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | `workloadmanager` | `golang:1.25-alpine` | `alpine:3.19` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `agentcube-router` | `golang:1.25-alpine` | `alpine:3.19` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `picod` | `golang:1.25-alpine` | `alpine:3.19` | `picod` (UID 1000) |\n\n### Multi-stage build pattern (all three):\n```\nStage 1 (builder): golang:1.25-alpine → CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\"\nStage 2 (runtime): alpine:3.19 → COPY binary, adduser -D -u 1000, USER, EXPOSE/ENTRYPOINT\n```\n\n### Other workspaces have already implemented Dockerfiles:\n- `MiniMax-M2.5` workspace has `docker/base.Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager`, `docker/Dockerfile.agentd` with Makefile integration\n\n---\n\n## 5. AR-032 / ST-3 / Docker Module Specs\n\n### AR-032 Definition (from `scripts/report.py` line 112):\n```\nAR-032: \"Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\"\n  module: docker\n  lang: Dockerfile\n  type: 新功能\n  size: S\n  est_loc: 150\n  est_files: 3\n  est_tasks: 3\n```\n\n### Base spec reference (from `specs/deployment/spec.md` lines 77-84):\n```markdown\n### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\nThe system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`),\nRouter (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n- **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n- **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from\n  Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n```\n\n### AR-032 delta-spec.md (fully populated, 151 lines):\nContains 6 requirements with 20 GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios covering:\n1. Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage) -- 7 scenarios\n2. Router Dockerfile (multi-stage) -- 5 scenarios\n3. PicoD Dockerfile (multi-stage) -- 4 scenarios\n4. Build context and reproducibility -- 3 scenarios\n5. Docker build output integrity -- 3 scenarios\n6. File Changes table (4 files)\n\n### AR-032 design.md (fully populated, 506 lines):\nContains complete technical design including architecture, data structures (3-image parameter matrix), API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps, and follow-up changes.\n\n### AR-032 proposal.md (scaffold, 41 lines):\nContains TODO placeholders -- not yet filled in.\n\n### AR-032 tasks.md (scaffold, 40 lines):\nContains TODO placeholders -- not yet filled in. This is the file that needs to be populated.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Path Where tasks.md Should Be Created/Populated\n\nThe tasks.md file already exists as a scaffold at:\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md`**\n\nIt needs to be populated following the **Format A** convention (as seen in AR-030 and AR-031), with:\n- Metadata block filled in (Module: docker, Language: Dockerfile, Size: S, Precondition: Stage ST-3 completed)\n- Task groups (T-001, T-002, etc.) with sub-tasks based on the delta-spec.md requirements\n- Each task group ending with a `**验收**: <command>` line\n- Dependency Graph (ASCII art)\n- Parallelizable Groups table\n- Acceptance Criteria table\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285922dcfffeNBQRq5vYutfPNT","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775875510829,"end":1775875629912}}}}
